doctype html
head
  meta(charset='utf-8')
  meta(name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1')
  title Duban Case Study - Desmond Chen
  link(rel='icon' type='image/x-icon' href='/css/img/icons/MainIcon.ico')
  link(rel='preconnect' href='https://fonts.googleapis.com')
  link(rel='preconnect' href='https://fonts.gstatic.com' crossorigin='')
  script(src='/JavaScript/dropdown.js' defer='')
  script(src='/JavaScript/fadeIn.js' defer='')
  link(href='/css/main.css' rel='stylesheet')
include inc/_navCase
main
  section
    img.caseImg(alt='Duban Chess Board in use' src='/css/img/DubanImg/DubanHeader.avif' height='600' weight='1000')
    .caseContainer
      div
        h1.caseTitle Duban 
        h1.caseTitle Chess Set
        p.projectCaseSubTitle School Project
      div
        p.descriptionSubhead Summary
        h2.descriptionHeader
          | Duban makes chess accessible for the 6 million Canadians with
          | arthritis, preserving elegance and easing play.
        hr
        .descriptionRoles
          div
            p.roleTitles Role
            p 3D Modelling &amp; Rendering, Physical Prototyping, Research &amp; Ideation
          div
            p.roleTitles Tools
            p
              | Solidworks + Visualize,
              | 3D Printing,
              | Laser Cutting
          div
            p.roleTitles Duration
            p 4 weeks, Fall 2024
          div
            p.roleTitles Team
            p Kate Simeonoff (Researcher), Nadine Elkabir (3D Modelling &amp; Rendering) 
  section
    .caseContainer.grayBG
      img.caseMeImg(src='/css/img/AlbertImg/DrawingMe.svg' alt='Drawing of me with a sword out in the open')
      div
        h2.whyStatementHead The Problem
        p
          | The manual dexterity needed to grip chess pieces causes frustration for users with arthritis,
          | leading many longtime chess enthusiasts to give up a cherished leisure and social activity.
          | While existing accessibility solutions (including our own concepts) offer greater comfort, they
          | lack the simplicity and elegance of a traditional chess set, a crucial part of the experience.
  section.projectSection
    .albertResearch
      p Ideation
      h3.explanationHeading
        | Generating broad solutions on pen and paper and deciding on what to push
        | forward to prototyping.
    .dubanExplanationTripleGrid
      figure
        img.chessPieceSketch(alt='Sketch with holes for hooks' src='/css/img/DubanImg/Sketches/ChessSketchDes.avif' height='200' width='400')
        figcaption Using a finger hook and holes in the chess pieces
      figure
        img.chessPieceSketch(src='/css/img/DubanImg/Sketches/ChessSketchKate.avif' alt='Sketch with hourglass shape Pieces' height='200' width='400')
        figcaption Hourglass shaped pieces
      figure
        img.chessPieceSketch(src='/css/img/DubanImg/Sketches/ChessSketchNed.avif' alt='Sketch with holes and high friction Pieces' height='200' width='400')
        figcaption Pin and holes with grips
  section.projectSection
    .dubanFoamGrid
      div
        p Early Foam Prototypes
        h3.explanationHeading
          | Through prototype testing, I discovered a key winning feature:
          | a
          | wine glass-inspired design eliminating the need for gripping.
        ul.dubanpointList
          li
            | I melted larger sheets of plastic together before cutting them to size, which allowed me to
            | account for any shrinkage.
          li
            | Retesting the heating temperature helped me find the ideal melting temperature with the heat
            | press, optimizing for durability and smoothness.
          li
            | I decided to repurpose an old nylon bag strap to ensure my sheath&rsquo;s strap was reliable in
            | the long term.
      .dubanFoamPhotoGrid
        img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/PrototypeFinger.avif')
        img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/Finger Hook.avif')
        img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/Grip.avif')
  section.projectSection
    p Refinement
    h3.explanationHeading.shrink Magnetizing towards a clearer direction
    p.shrink
      | Instead of pegs, magnets were able to snap the pieces in place and could easily be
      | repositioned. They
      | also prevented tipping which was our main pain point when error occurred in natural play. The piece
      | designs were streamlined and given removable heads for gameplay purpose - A pawn that reached the end of
      | the board could easily swap out its head with that of any other piece.
    .dubanRefinementImageFlex
      figure
        img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/New Drafts.avif')
        figcaption Considering the magnetized base and removable heads for piece promotion.
      figure
        img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/MeassuredPieces.avif')
        figcaption Creating standardized bodies to be digitized.
  section.projectSection
    .dubanFoamGrid
      div
        p Early Foam Prototypes
        h3.explanationHeading
          | Through prototype testing, I discovered a key winning feature:
          | a
          | wine glass-inspired design eliminating the need for gripping.
        ul.dubanpointList
          li
            | I melted larger sheets of plastic together before cutting them to size, which allowed me to
            | account for any shrinkage.
          li
            | Retesting the heating temperature helped me find the ideal melting temperature with the heat
            | press, optimizing for durability and smoothness.
          li
            | I decided to repurpose an old nylon bag strap to ensure my sheath&rsquo;s strap was reliable in
            | the long term.
      img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/FabricatedThings.avif')
  section.darkGrayBG.projectSection
    p.finalSubHeading.whiteText Final Physical Product
    h3.explanationHeading.whiteText.shrink
      | The final prototype made it clear that more comfortable chess for players with arthritis is not only
      | possible but can also remain as elegant and recognizable as the traditional experience.
    .finalDubanGrid
      img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/ChessMagnetClose.avif' height='483' width='363' alt='Close up of magnets in board and piece')
      img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/PieceOnBoard.avif' height='483' width='363' alt='Pieces placed on the board')
      img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/HouseShot.avif' height='483' width='363' alt='Board Placed in a room')
  section.projectSection.overHeadPadding
    p Modeling and Rendering
    h3.explanationHeading.shrink
      | Refining the final concept in Solidworks, with material considerations
    p.shrink
      | Instead of a painted aesthetic that could wear away, I decided on a multi wood
      | construction that gives a more classic and refined appearance. Softer materials such as felt and velour
      | were added to the pieces and shelf to reduce noise during use and transport.
    img.dubanRenderImage(src='/css/img/DubanImg/3DRender.avif')
    p.shrink
      | All the models were made in a combination of Blender, OnShape and Solidworks, then they
      | were compiled and rendered in SolidWorks Visualize. The goal was to create a chess set that would fit in
      | any classic home, so the furniture was chosen to reflect that feeling.
    .dubanRenderGrid
      figure
        img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/Chess.avif')
        figcaption Set up for gameplay
      figure
        img(src='/css/img/DubanImg/ChessSetup.avif')
        figcaption Chess set in use
include inc/_footer